| **Execution**            | Command and Scripting Interpreter                                             | Once access is gained, attackers can execute scripts or commands that leverage the vulnerability to manipulate the FPU state. |
| **Persistence**          | Boot or Logon Autostart Execution                                            | Attackers may install backdoors or scripts that utilize the vulnerability to maintain persistence across reboots. |
| **Privilege Escalation** | Exploitation of Vulnerability in Kernel                                       | By exploiting CVE-2024-35801, attackers can escalate privileges, allowing them to execute code with higher permissions. |
| **Defense Evasion**      | Obfuscated Files or Information                                               | Attackers may obfuscate their payloads or scripts to evade detection by security software. |
| **Impact**               | Data Manipulation                                                             | Successful exploitation can lead to unauthorized data manipulation or access to sensitive information. |

